When I was boy and I would see scary things in the news, my mother would say to me, ‚ÄúLook for the helpers. You will always find people who are helping.‚Äù
~Fred Rogers

4th graders learned about a young man named Welles Crowther who was working on the 104th floor of the South Towers on 9/11 who selflessly saved 12 people before paying the ultimate price with his life.

Students read the book üìö The Man In The Red Bandana and watched a documentary that detailed his courageous act of bravery. After a great discussion on the qualities and characteristics of a ‚Äúhero‚Äù, students made Bandanas of Bravery where they wrote some of the characteristics and feelings Welles‚Äô portrayed through his actions on September 11, 2001 üá∫üá∏‚ù§Ô∏è
#loomiswolves #neverforget #fourthgraderocks

post_text: Today was supposed to be Loomis Graduation for our 2020 Seniors. Instead, we held a photo opportunity for graduates and their parents, as the students received their diploma. I would like to commend this year‚Äôs Senior class and their parents, families, and friends. This is not the way any of us wanted to end the year. Our Seniors have been short-changed on so many major events during their last quarter of school. Today my heart breaks for their losses, but today also gives me hope for our future. These twelve students know and understand what adversity is and will meet any challenge they will face in life. I salute and THANK our Seniors for their patience, hard work, and perseverance. Congratulations LOOMIS Seniors! You will be missed!
